{
  "texts": [
    "Recent advances in data integration have made it possible to simulate the dynamics of pest spread in a realistic manner.",
    "For example, the continental spread pathways of the airborne wheat stem rust (Puccinia graminis f. sp.",
    "tritici) were studied using Lagrangian simulations of air mass movement (Meyer et al. 2017).",
    "This framework has been adapted into a real-time early warning system for rapid disease outbreak response by policymakers (Allen-Sader et al. 2019).",
    "Combining such connectivity models with species distribution models (see \"Environmental criterion\" section) may be a promising way to prioritize surveillance to the most connected suitable environments for a pest."
  ]
}